OVERVIEW: Create a new scheme for a target

USAGE: xcodeproj-cli create-scheme [--project <project>] [--workspace <workspace>] [--verbose] [--dry-run] <scheme-name> [--target <target>] [--shared] [--user]

ARGUMENTS:
  <scheme-name>           Name of the scheme to create

OPTIONS:
  -p, --project <project> Path to .xcodeproj file (default: looks for
                          *.xcodeproj in current directory)
  -w, --workspace <workspace>
                          Path to .xcworkspace file
  -V, --verbose           Enable verbose output with performance metrics
  --dry-run               Preview changes without saving
  --target <target>       Target to create scheme for (default: scheme name)
  --shared                Create as shared scheme (default)
  --user                  Create as user-specific scheme
  --version               Show the version.
  -h, --help              Show help information.

